{"title_page": "The Last Podcast on the Left", "text_new": "{{Infobox Podcast\n| width = 200em\n| title = The Last Podcast on the Left\n| image = LastPod_logo.jpg\n| caption = \n| hosting = {{ubl|Ben Kissel|Marcus Parks|[[Henry Zebrowski]]}}\n| language = [[English language|English]]\n| updates = Twice-weekly\n| length = About 1 hour<ref>{{cite web |title=Last Podcast On The Left |url=https://www.podchaser.com/podcasts/last-podcast-on-the-left-33097 |website=Podchaser |accessdate=9 July 2019}}</ref>\n| audio format = MP3\n| num_episodes = 512\n| began = {{Start date|2011}}\n| ended = \n| subjects = \n| genre = {{Hlist|Comedy|[[true crime]]|dark comedy|paranormal}}\n| provider = [[Spotify]]\n| url = {{URL|https://www.lastpodcastontheleft.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Last Podcast on the Left''''' is a weekly [[podcast]] on the Last Podcast Network<ref>https://www.lastpodcastnetwork.com/</ref> featuring comedian and podcast host Ben Kissel, podcast producer and researcher Marcus Parks, and comedian and actor [[Henry Zebrowski]] (who joined in the third episode), all of whom are longtime friends. With a main episode released each Friday and a Side Stories episode released once a week, the episodes are generally one to two hours in length, with the hosts exploring the horrors of the world both imagined and real. Previous episodes have explored the topics of serial killers, conspiracy theories, UFO sightings, ghosts, and readings of fan-submitted [[creepypasta]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/marc-hershon/podcast-review-the-last-p_b_11152446.html|title= Podcast Review: The Last Podcast On The Left |date= July 23, 2016|accessdate= April 11, 2017}}</ref> Kissel, Parks, and Zebrowski tour with live performances of the podcast and produce ''The Last Stream on the Left'', a live-streaming spin-off show on the [[Adult Swim]] website.\n\nSeveral repeat characters are present on the podcast, primarily voiced by Zebrowski, such as \"Detective Popcorn\" (the semi-erotic food-focused incompetent police detective), [[Charles Ng]] (a notorious serial killer), \"Terry the Gnome\", and Minnie and Nannie Williams (victims of serial killer [[H. H. Holmes]]). \n\nThe opening theme of the podcast features snippets from serial killers, such as [[Jeffrey Dahmer]] who utters the line, \"That's when the cannibalism started.\" It also includes the line and subsequent advertisement transition \"Rise from your grave!\" uttered by [[Zeus]] from the [[Sega]] action game ''[[Altered Beast]]''. The closing theme is [[Al Bowlly]]'s \"[[Midnight, the Stars and You]]\", a reference to ''[[The Shining (film)|The Shining]]''.\n\nOn November 19, 2019, it was announced that the show was moving exclusively to [[Spotify]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/last-podcast-left-moving-exclusively-spotify-1256236|title='Last Podcast on the Left' Moving Exclusively to Spotify|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> for ad sponsored episodes. \n\nIn 2017, ''The Last Podcast on the Left'' received the People's Voice [[Webby award|Webby]] in the Podcasts & Digital Audio (Comedy) category.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.webbyawards.com/winners/2017/podcasts-digital-audio/general-podcasts/comedy/the-last-podcast-on-the-left/|title=The Last Podcast On The Left {{!}} The Webby Awards|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, [[Houghton Mifflin Harcourt]] released ''The Last Book on the Left'', written by Kissel, Parks, and Zebrowski.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hmhbooks.com/shop/books/The-Last-Book-on-the-Left/9781328566317|title=The Last Book on the Left: Stories of Murder and Mayhem from History\u2019s Most Notorious Serial Killers {{!}} HMH Books|website=www.hmhbooks.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/last-podcast-on-the-left-book-interview.html|title=The Last Podcast on the Left Hosts Break Down the Art of True-Crime Comedy| website=Vulture|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n== Last Stream on the Left ==\n\nThe Last Stream on the Left is a spin-off show hosted on the Adult Swim website. There are 6 seasons and a total of 106 episodes available on the [[Adult Swim]] website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adultswim.com/videos/last-stream-on-the-left|title=Last Stream on the Left|last=|first=|date=|website=Adult Swim|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=November 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n[[List of Last Podcast on the Left episodes]] including Side Stories.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http:/www.lastpodcastnetwork.com/}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Last Podcast on the Left}}\n[[Category:Comedy and humor podcasts]]\n[[Category:Talk podcasts]]\n[[Category:Audio podcasts]]\n[[Category:Non-fiction works about serial killers]]\n[[Category:Crime podcasts]]\n[[Category:2011 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Horror podcasts]]\n", "text_old": "{{Infobox Podcast\n| width = 200em\n| title = The Last Podcast on the Left\n| image = LastPod_logo.jpg\n| caption = \n| hosting = {{ubl|Ben Kissel|Marcus Parks|[[Henry Zebrowski]]}}\n| language = [[English language|English]]\n| updates = Twice-weekly\n| length = About 1 hour<ref>{{cite web |title=Last Podcast On The Left |url=https://www.podchaser.com/podcasts/last-podcast-on-the-left-33097 |website=Podchaser |accessdate=9 July 2019}}</ref>\n| audio format = MP3\n| num_episodes = 508\n| began = {{Start date|2011}}\n| ended = \n| subjects = \n| genre = {{Hlist|Comedy|[[true crime]]|dark comedy|paranormal}}\n| provider = [[Spotify]]\n| url = {{URL|https://www.lastpodcastontheleft.com/}}\n}}\n\n'''''The Last Podcast on the Left''''' is a weekly [[podcast]] on the Last Podcast Network<ref>https://www.lastpodcastnetwork.com/</ref> featuring comedian and podcast host Ben Kissel, podcast producer and researcher Marcus Parks, and comedian and actor [[Henry Zebrowski]] (who joined in the third episode), all of whom are longtime friends. With a main episode released each Friday and a Side Stories episode released once a week, the episodes are generally one to two hours in length, with the hosts exploring the horrors of the world both imagined and real. Previous episodes have explored the topics of serial killers, conspiracy theories, UFO sightings, ghosts, and readings of fan-submitted [[creepypasta]]s.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.huffingtonpost.com/marc-hershon/podcast-review-the-last-p_b_11152446.html|title= Podcast Review: The Last Podcast On The Left |date= July 23, 2016|accessdate= April 11, 2017}}</ref> Kissel, Parks, and Zebrowski tour with live performances of the podcast and produce ''The Last Stream on the Left'', a live-streaming spin-off show on the [[Adult Swim]] website.\n\nSeveral repeat characters are present on the podcast, primarily voiced by Zebrowski, such as \"Detective Popcorn\" (the semi-erotic food-focused incompetent police detective), [[Charles Ng]] (a notorious serial killer), \"Terry the Gnome\", and Minnie and Nannie Williams (victims of serial killer [[H. H. Holmes]]). \n\nThe opening theme of the podcast features snippets from serial killers, such as [[Jeffrey Dahmer]] who utters the line, \"That's when the cannibalism started.\" It also includes the line and subsequent advertisement transition \"Rise from your grave!\" uttered by [[Zeus]] from the [[Sega]] action game ''[[Altered Beast]]''. The closing theme is [[Al Bowlly]]'s \"[[Midnight, the Stars and You]]\", a reference to ''[[The Shining (film)|The Shining]]''.\n\nOn November 19, 2019, it was announced that the show was moving exclusively to [[Spotify]]<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hollywoodreporter.com/news/last-podcast-left-moving-exclusively-spotify-1256236|title='Last Podcast on the Left' Moving Exclusively to Spotify|website=The Hollywood Reporter|language=en|access-date=2019-11-20}}</ref> for ad sponsored episodes. \n\nIn 2017, ''The Last Podcast on the Left'' received the People's Voice [[Webby award|Webby]] in the Podcasts & Digital Audio (Comedy) category.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.webbyawards.com/winners/2017/podcasts-digital-audio/general-podcasts/comedy/the-last-podcast-on-the-left/|title=The Last Podcast On The Left {{!}} The Webby Awards|accessdate=September 13, 2018}}</ref>\n\nIn 2020, [[Houghton Mifflin Harcourt]] released ''The Last Book on the Left'', written by Kissel, Parks, and Zebrowski.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.hmhbooks.com/shop/books/The-Last-Book-on-the-Left/9781328566317|title=The Last Book on the Left: Stories of Murder and Mayhem from History\u2019s Most Notorious Serial Killers {{!}} HMH Books|website=www.hmhbooks.com|language=en|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.vulture.com/2020/04/last-podcast-on-the-left-book-interview.html|title=The Last Podcast on the Left Hosts Break Down the Art of True-Crime Comedy| website=Vulture|access-date=2019-12-16}}</ref>\n\n== Last Stream on the Left ==\n\nThe Last Stream on the Left is a spin-off show hosted on the Adult Swim website. There are 6 seasons and a total of 106 episodes available on the [[Adult Swim]] website.<ref>{{Cite web|url=https://www.adultswim.com/videos/last-stream-on-the-left|title=Last Stream on the Left|last=|first=|date=|website=Adult Swim|url-status=live|archive-url=|archive-date=|access-date=November 8, 2019}}</ref>\n\n==Episodes==\n[[List of Last Podcast on the Left episodes]] including Side Stories.\n\n==References==\n{{Reflist}}\n\n==External links==\n* {{Official website|http:/www.lastpodcastnetwork.com/}}\n\n{{DEFAULTSORT:Last Podcast on the Left}}\n[[Category:Comedy and humor podcasts]]\n[[Category:Talk podcasts]]\n[[Category:Audio podcasts]]\n[[Category:Non-fiction works about serial killers]]\n[[Category:Crime podcasts]]\n[[Category:2011 podcast debuts]]\n[[Category:Horror podcasts]]\n", "name_user": "TheMemeMonarch", "label": "safe", "comment": "updated counter", "url_page": "//en.wikipedia.org/wiki/The_Last_Podcast_on_